1
00:01:22,800 --> 00:01:24,160
Yeah, just like that.

2
00:01:25,280 --> 00:01:26,440
That's enough.

3
00:01:30,360 --> 00:01:31,800
Everything I teach you,

4
00:01:31,880 --> 00:01:34,000
I've tried it myself. It works.

5
00:01:34,080 --> 00:01:36,760
I became rich. You can become rich too.

6
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:38,440
-Rich!
-Rich!

7
00:01:46,160 --> 00:01:48,840
Cent's office is really grand!

8
00:01:48,920 --> 00:01:51,000
He must be really rich.

9
00:01:51,080 --> 00:01:52,000
No, wait.

10
00:01:52,600 --> 00:01:54,240
Super rich!

11
00:01:54,320 --> 00:01:55,480
Cent.

12
00:01:56,640 --> 00:01:58,720
If you don't learn to keep an open mind,

13
00:01:59,880 --> 00:02:04,480
someday you might end up
with nothing left.

14
00:02:07,560 --> 00:02:09,160
I'll start now.

15
00:02:11,240 --> 00:02:13,200
I want to build my own clothing brand.

16
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:14,760
My target customers

17
00:02:14,840 --> 00:02:17,320
are people who like streetwear,

18
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:20,520
but they don't like following trends.
I brought some references too.

19
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:22,720
These are rough ideas.

20
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:25,600
They'll be unique,
but still very personal.

21
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:28,400
My clothes can be bought all year round.

22
00:02:28,480 --> 00:02:30,880
Their prices are affordable.

23
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:33,480
And most importantly, our sales channels

24
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:36,960
will be both offline and online.

25
00:02:37,040 --> 00:02:38,360
My brand will be called

26
00:02:38,440 --> 00:02:42,160
DIY. Do It Yuan! Just do it, Yuan!

27
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:50,680
Finished?

28
00:02:51,720 --> 00:02:52,880
Yes.

29
00:02:53,480 --> 00:02:54,360
You may go.

30
00:02:56,040 --> 00:02:57,000
Well…

31
00:02:57,520 --> 00:02:58,360
Cent.

32
00:02:58,880 --> 00:03:01,520
Aren't you going to look
at my sketches or references?

33
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:07,720
I already did.

34
00:03:11,040 --> 00:03:13,160
-That's it?
-Yeah.

35
00:03:13,240 --> 00:03:15,200
That's enough.
That's all that's interesting.

36
00:03:15,720 --> 00:03:17,760
Don't you have any comments?

37
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:19,800
I'll give my comments all at once.
You may go.

38
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:31,280
<i>I want to open my own dessert shop.</i>

39
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:34,880
My main customers are people
who enjoy a variety of desserts.

40
00:03:34,960 --> 00:03:37,520
What they're buying
is something both delicious

41
00:03:37,600 --> 00:03:39,520
and visually appealing.

42
00:03:39,600 --> 00:03:41,280
My plan

43
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:43,840
is to open shops along BTS stations

44
00:03:43,920 --> 00:03:45,880
or near office buildings.

45
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:49,200
The reason people will buy my desserts

46
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:51,320
is because they're delicious

47
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:53,120
and there's a wide variety to choose from.

48
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:55,120
I already have a name for my shop.

49
00:03:55,200 --> 00:03:57,960
It's La Prime by Bonus.

50
00:03:58,040 --> 00:04:00,960
Here are all the documents I've prepared,

51
00:04:01,040 --> 00:04:03,200
in case you'd like to take a closer look.

52
00:04:09,360 --> 00:04:10,680
I don't want to look at them.

53
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:13,720
Next.

54
00:04:15,480 --> 00:04:16,959
My name is Franc.

55
00:04:17,880 --> 00:04:19,839
I guess this is our first time meeting.

56
00:04:21,560 --> 00:04:23,120
I was Peace's girlfriend.

57
00:04:25,320 --> 00:04:27,320
Does that have anything to do
with your presentation?

58
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:30,480
Kind of, but not really.

59
00:04:30,560 --> 00:04:32,400
I don't like drama.

60
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:34,680
If you're here to talk business, talk.

61
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:57,440
After Peace passed away,

62
00:04:57,520 --> 00:05:01,240
I started getting more attention.
My Instagram

63
00:05:01,320 --> 00:05:03,600
and fan pages grew a lot.

64
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:07,200
Now I even get clients asking me to post.

65
00:05:07,280 --> 00:05:10,200
The response has been great.

66
00:05:10,280 --> 00:05:13,800
So I've been thinking
about becoming an influencer.

67
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:17,280
I also want to have my own YouTube channel

68
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:21,520
for people who want to follow me,
share their experiences,

69
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:24,160
and comment. I want
to build a small community

70
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:27,000
for my supporters, and--

71
00:05:27,080 --> 00:05:28,400
Enough.

72
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:29,800
I wasn't done talking yet.

73
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:33,840
If you start like this,
the rest will just be repetition,

74
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:35,360
with no new points made.

75
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:39,200
That's it?

76
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:40,400
That's it.

77
00:05:41,640 --> 00:05:42,960
I'll give my comments all at once.

78
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:51,480
The other two, come in.

79
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:55,880
I'll give my comments all at once

80
00:05:56,480 --> 00:05:59,000
because what I'm going to say
to all of you is the same thing.

81
00:05:59,080 --> 00:05:59,800
And I don't like--

82
00:05:59,880 --> 00:06:00,920
-Repetition.
-Repetition.

83
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:05,360
You want your own businesses,

84
00:06:05,440 --> 00:06:08,400
fashion brand, dessert shop,
YouTube channel,

85
00:06:08,480 --> 00:06:12,720
but you don't know anything
about business, not even the basics.

86
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:16,200
Many people start businesses
without knowing anything and succeed.

87
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:18,200
How do you know they knew nothing?

88
00:06:18,280 --> 00:06:20,480
Well, that's what they say
during interviews.

89
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:23,280
They learned along the way
from their mistakes.

90
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:24,560
Then feel free to leave.

91
00:06:25,960 --> 00:06:27,960
Go make mistakes, go out of business,

92
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:30,920
and learn from failure yourselves.

93
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:33,120
So I don't have to waste my time.
Go ahead.

94
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:34,920
I'm sorry on behalf of my friend.

95
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,600
Why are you apologizing for me?

96
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:38,960
Franc, enough.

97
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:42,080
If you want to have your own business,

98
00:06:42,160 --> 00:06:45,680
just wanting it isn't enough.
You need knowledge too.

99
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:47,080
-You.
-Yes.

100
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:49,840
You want to start a clothing brand.
Do you understand design?

101
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:52,720
Tailoring, pattern-making, sewing,
production capacity?

102
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:55,480
Unique but affordable.
So where's the profit?

103
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:57,920
Which shops will sell it?
How much do they take?

104
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,720
How many pieces do you need to break even?

105
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:02,160
Too many and it's not unique.
Too few and it's not profitable.

106
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:04,960
In the end, ask yourself this.
Do you want to be a clothing seller

107
00:07:05,040 --> 00:07:06,720
or a designer? They are not the same.

108
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:08,400
-And you!
-Yes.

109
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:09,840
You want to open a dessert shop.

110
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:12,360
Do you know how many dessert shops
there are in Bangkok?

111
00:07:12,440 --> 00:07:14,280
Including online,
how many shops are there?

112
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:16,840
Most of them are homemade.
What makes yours different from them?

113
00:07:16,920 --> 00:07:19,040
A lot of variety
means a lot of production.

114
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:20,840
If you can't sell everything, then what?

115
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:23,200
Throw it away? Your strength is variety.

116
00:07:23,280 --> 00:07:26,800
But do you even have a signature?
If you don't, you're going to fail.

117
00:07:29,960 --> 00:07:31,320
As for you…

118
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:35,920
No comment.

119
00:07:36,520 --> 00:07:38,200
Why don't I get any feedback?

120
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:43,680
You're not serious, just here for fun.
I won't waste my time commenting.

121
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:45,920
But I am serious.

122
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:48,120
I'm going to become an influencer.

123
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:49,920
What is an influencer?

124
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,920
How is it different
from a content creator?

125
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,840
What are KOLs and KOCs?

126
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:56,320
Mega, macro, micro, nano,
how do you measure them?

127
00:07:58,120 --> 00:07:59,120
Answer!

128
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:06,960
Being an influencer isn't easy.

129
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:08,480
Not everyone can be one,

130
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:11,080
especially someone delusional
like you. It's too far.

131
00:08:11,960 --> 00:08:13,240
Stop dreaming.

132
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:21,640
I told you it's a waste of time.

133
00:08:21,720 --> 00:08:24,040
It's like being on <i>Shark Tank</i>.

134
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:27,320
This is the smart guy you talked about?
He just insults people.

135
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:29,920
Hey.

136
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:31,920
Why are you yelling at Fuang?

137
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:34,320
She didn't know he'd say all that.

138
00:08:35,559 --> 00:08:38,000
Is he this harsh when he talks to you too?

139
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:41,600
Honestly, he was even worse with me.

140
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:44,120
I lost my confidence back then too.

141
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:48,680
Then why did he still fund you?

142
00:08:49,520 --> 00:08:51,000
I don't even know.

143
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:53,920
But I'm sorry, guys.

144
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:56,800
I didn't think he'd be this harsh.

145
00:08:57,720 --> 00:08:58,720
Don't be sorry.

146
00:08:59,560 --> 00:09:00,920
It's not your fault.

147
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:02,800
And honestly, most of what he said

148
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:04,680
was true.

149
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:07,400
Actually, it's all true.

150
00:09:09,040 --> 00:09:10,520
I don't know about you guys,

151
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:12,480
but I don't accept it,
and I don't believe it

152
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:13,560
because I'm not just dreaming.

153
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:16,360
I'm going to make it real. Just watch.

154
00:09:17,560 --> 00:09:20,040
You're leaving? I'll go check on her.

155
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:21,960
Don't overthink it.

156
00:09:22,040 --> 00:09:24,440
Even if I just got shot down,
thanks anyway.

157
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:35,720
Yuan's right.

158
00:09:36,760 --> 00:09:38,080
Don't overthink it.

159
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:41,280
Just go back to work.

160
00:09:41,880 --> 00:09:44,360
He is super strict.

161
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:47,240
He wouldn't like you hanging around here,
chatting with us.

162
00:09:52,440 --> 00:09:54,160
Good luck then.

163
00:09:57,160 --> 00:09:58,000
I'll head off now.

164
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:13,920
Are you okay?

165
00:10:15,640 --> 00:10:16,600
Well, deal with it.

166
00:10:16,680 --> 00:10:19,640
If you're serious about business,
it'll get even harder than this.

167
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:21,880
What do you mean?

168
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:23,560
Like getting scolded by customers.

169
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:27,680
In person, on social media.
And if you sell on an app,

170
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:29,600
one-star reviews
feel like the end of the world.

171
00:10:29,680 --> 00:10:32,840
If you're shaken by criticism,
you won't make it.

172
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:38,480
But you didn't have to say it so harshly.

173
00:10:40,960 --> 00:10:45,600
How am I being harsh?
Everything I said is the truth.

174
00:10:46,640 --> 00:10:48,680
If you think it's not true,
then argue back.

175
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,800
When I rejected your work before

176
00:10:50,880 --> 00:10:53,760
and you explained your reasons,
did I not listen?

177
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:57,560
You did.

178
00:10:58,320 --> 00:11:00,840
But your friends were all silent.

179
00:11:00,920 --> 00:11:03,560
That means none of them
had stronger reasons to counter it.

180
00:11:04,720 --> 00:11:05,920
Am I right?

181
00:11:07,280 --> 00:11:10,840
I've talked to your friends.
Don't forget our agreement.

182
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:14,160
Work 24/7 with full commitment.
Don't forget.

183
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:19,840
I won't.

184
00:11:19,920 --> 00:11:20,960
Good.

185
00:11:21,640 --> 00:11:23,160
Before you think about others,

186
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:24,880
make sure you can survive.

187
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:31,280
Those friends you say are close to you,
are you sure they really care?

188
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:35,400
Why are you asking me that?

189
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:37,800
I was just curious.

190
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:42,480
We've been friends since we were kids,

191
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:44,960
and we'll stay like this until we're old.

192
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:49,000
Even if I can't fully support myself yet,

193
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:51,760
if I have a chance to help my friends,
I'll do it to the very end.

194
00:11:56,760 --> 00:12:00,600
Someone without friends like you
probably wouldn't understand.

195
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:09,240
I'll go get my notebook,
so we can start working.

196
00:12:26,280 --> 00:12:28,040
-Calmed down yet?
-No.

197
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:31,320
No one's ever talked to me like that.
That's too disrespectful.

198
00:12:33,280 --> 00:12:35,040
If it's a scammer, I'm gonna…

199
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:38,760
Hello, Elle.

200
00:12:38,840 --> 00:12:41,920
Hi, Franc. We've got feedback
from the client.

201
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,680
They really like your work.

202
00:12:43,760 --> 00:12:46,360
They want to buy out the content
for use in a printed ad.

203
00:12:47,560 --> 00:12:48,880
What is it?

204
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:51,880
The client wants to purchase
the photo for further use.

205
00:12:51,960 --> 00:12:54,480
They'll pay you for it. Is that okay?

206
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:59,200
Okay. If the client thinks it's suitable,
I'm fine with it.

207
00:12:59,280 --> 00:13:01,760
In that case,
send the original files to me.

208
00:13:01,840 --> 00:13:03,960
The buyout fee is 100,000 baht.

209
00:13:04,040 --> 00:13:06,480
A hundred thousand!
They're paying a hundred thousand?

210
00:13:07,160 --> 00:13:09,840
<i>Yes. I'll send over</i>
<i>the contract shortly as well.</i>

211
00:13:09,920 --> 00:13:12,880
Okay, Elle. Thank you so much.

212
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:15,240
Yes, goodbye.

213
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:20,360
Hey! Hear that? We worked on it
for a few hours, and the client loved it.

214
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:21,840
They're buying it for an extra 100,000.

215
00:13:21,920 --> 00:13:23,920
Wow!

216
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:26,760
This just proves
that what Cent said isn't true.

217
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:29,480
He said being an influencer
isn't easy, right?

218
00:13:29,560 --> 00:13:32,240
I'm going to prove him wrong. You too.

219
00:13:32,320 --> 00:13:35,360
Don't listen to what he said.
Just do whatever you want.

220
00:13:36,040 --> 00:13:36,880
Got it?

221
00:13:36,960 --> 00:13:40,480
Don't let a few words from someone
you just met decide your life.

222
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:42,680
Be confident, and go for it.

223
00:13:45,560 --> 00:13:48,320
Honestly, I don't even want Fuang
working with him.

224
00:13:49,040 --> 00:13:51,080
We met him for five minutes,
and he already tore us down.

225
00:13:51,160 --> 00:13:53,240
Imagine what he'll do to her.

226
00:13:53,320 --> 00:13:54,560
I'm going to tell her to quit.

227
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:02,240
What exactly do you want me to do?

228
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:04,680
Do research on daily wage workers.

229
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:06,400
Yes.

230
00:14:13,880 --> 00:14:15,040
That's it?

231
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:16,160
Yeah, that's it.

232
00:14:18,280 --> 00:14:20,800
Isn't that too broad?

233
00:14:21,800 --> 00:14:23,600
That's all the client briefed us on.

234
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:25,280
Is it Aunt Eiang?

235
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:29,480
What exactly did she brief you on?

236
00:14:30,080 --> 00:14:34,760
I want you to do something
that makes day-to-day workers richer.

237
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:36,400
Wow.

238
00:14:37,120 --> 00:14:38,560
That's a tough brief.

239
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:40,600
Before I write the program,

240
00:14:40,680 --> 00:14:44,400
I want as much data as possible.
Get it fast and have it ready by tomorrow.

241
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:45,520
Tomorrow?

242
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:50,400
Tomorrow. No need to repeat it.
Tomorrow it is.

243
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:55,000
I'll go gather the data now.

244
00:14:55,080 --> 00:14:57,600
See you here tomorrow, right?

245
00:14:58,200 --> 00:14:59,000
Yeah.

246
00:14:59,080 --> 00:15:00,320
Okay.

247
00:15:03,920 --> 00:15:05,160
Goodbye.

248
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:27,400
Bonus.

249
00:15:29,480 --> 00:15:31,160
Hey, we're here.

250
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:34,240
Oh.

251
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:36,040
Thanks.

252
00:15:39,440 --> 00:15:40,320
Bonus.

253
00:15:42,520 --> 00:15:43,440
Are you okay?

254
00:15:49,680 --> 00:15:50,720
Not really.

255
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:57,080
Honestly, after hearing what he said,
I feel really discouraged.

256
00:15:58,800 --> 00:16:00,320
I really am useless, aren't I?

257
00:16:01,840 --> 00:16:07,240
Like my dad said, I can't do business.
It'll just end up failing.

258
00:16:08,880 --> 00:16:11,800
I guess that's true.

259
00:16:59,720 --> 00:17:01,440
Our daughter's really serious about this.

260
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:02,800
<i>I didn't pass the teacher exam.</i>

261
00:17:02,880 --> 00:17:06,400
But I'm not retaking it.
I want to sell desserts.

262
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:08,079
What made you think of this?

263
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:10,400
When I make desserts, I'm happy.

264
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:13,160
I feel like I've been connected to it
since I was a kid.

265
00:17:13,240 --> 00:17:15,079
Like it's always been inside me.

266
00:17:16,160 --> 00:17:18,359
Being determined doesn't mean
you'll succeed.

267
00:17:22,160 --> 00:17:24,520
Do I really look that bad to you, Dad?

268
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:30,680
Bonus, he didn't mean it like that.

269
00:17:31,680 --> 00:17:34,040
Not bad, just careless.

270
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:37,600
You're impulsive, reckless, and stubborn.

271
00:17:40,080 --> 00:17:41,080
I'm not stubborn.

272
00:17:42,640 --> 00:17:45,480
I just want to do something
that makes me happy.

273
00:17:46,440 --> 00:17:48,200
But don't worry, Dad.

274
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:51,120
I won't do it anymore. I give up!

275
00:17:51,880 --> 00:17:53,080
Bonus.

276
00:17:54,800 --> 00:17:58,960
Kids these days do whatever they want.
If they feel like quitting,

277
00:17:59,040 --> 00:18:00,640
they quit that easily.

278
00:18:01,240 --> 00:18:06,240
I quit because no one ever supported me.

279
00:18:06,320 --> 00:18:08,560
No one has ever believed in me
that I can do it.

280
00:18:08,640 --> 00:18:11,920
No one has ever given me any confidence.

281
00:18:12,840 --> 00:18:15,360
I just need someone

282
00:18:15,920 --> 00:18:17,840
to believe in me, that I can do it.

283
00:18:19,880 --> 00:18:23,440
If someone had given me that confidence,
I would've kept fighting,

284
00:18:23,520 --> 00:18:25,160
but there wasn't anyone.

285
00:18:25,760 --> 00:18:30,080
Not a single person. I don't know
what I'm fighting for anymore.

286
00:18:47,680 --> 00:18:49,200
If I invest in Bonus's business,

287
00:18:49,800 --> 00:18:51,760
would you let her do it?

288
00:19:02,680 --> 00:19:05,320
I'll put in the money,
she will put in the effort.

289
00:19:05,920 --> 00:19:08,400
If you're worried about management,

290
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:11,040
I'll handle the finances, sales,

291
00:19:11,120 --> 00:19:14,480
and marketing myself. If you can trust me…

292
00:19:20,040 --> 00:19:22,000
It's not as easy as you think, Pound.

293
00:19:22,760 --> 00:19:25,280
In this economy, there are only sellers.

294
00:19:25,360 --> 00:19:28,880
Very few buyers.
You're just throwing your money away.

295
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:30,720
I've already thought it through.

296
00:19:31,640 --> 00:19:34,280
We'll start with a small rented space,

297
00:19:34,360 --> 00:19:36,280
with no seating, as a market test.

298
00:19:37,160 --> 00:19:40,800
If it works,
we'll expand to a bigger place.

299
00:19:41,480 --> 00:19:45,080
As for marketing, income, and expenses,
I'll handle everything.

300
00:19:45,160 --> 00:19:48,280
If we start seeing losses
or things look bad,

301
00:19:48,360 --> 00:19:49,960
we'll shut it down before it gets serious.

302
00:19:50,040 --> 00:19:53,720
But I don't think it'll come to that.

303
00:19:57,440 --> 00:19:58,720
I believe she can do it.

304
00:20:10,240 --> 00:20:12,200
I think this is actually a good idea.

305
00:20:12,840 --> 00:20:16,680
Pound has a degree
in this field, after all. If he helps,

306
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:18,320
you won't have to worry so much.

307
00:20:24,720 --> 00:20:26,000
Alright, fine.

308
00:20:31,560 --> 00:20:34,000
But I don't want you
to abandon the teacher exam.

309
00:20:35,080 --> 00:20:37,480
If you could do both, that would be best.

310
00:20:38,080 --> 00:20:40,840
A stable job is still better.

311
00:20:41,440 --> 00:20:42,800
Yes, Dad.

312
00:20:43,720 --> 00:20:46,520
I'll do my best to handle both.

313
00:21:25,320 --> 00:21:26,480
<i>Pound.</i>

314
00:21:26,560 --> 00:21:28,560
You're not joking, right?

315
00:21:28,640 --> 00:21:30,800
You're not lying just to help me, are you?

316
00:21:30,880 --> 00:21:34,040
No one jokes about money and investment.

317
00:21:34,560 --> 00:21:38,400
Go find a place to open your shop.
Talk to me about the investment.

318
00:21:38,480 --> 00:21:39,760
I'll be your investor.

319
00:21:42,080 --> 00:21:43,800
Hey.

320
00:21:43,880 --> 00:21:46,960
Why are you crying again? What's wrong?

321
00:21:48,760 --> 00:21:50,440
I'm just happy.

322
00:21:51,760 --> 00:21:52,960
Thank you.

323
00:21:55,120 --> 00:21:57,840
Thank you for believing I can do it.

324
00:21:59,240 --> 00:22:00,960
You're so silly.

325
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:03,600
It's nothing.

326
00:22:03,680 --> 00:22:06,440
Don't worry. I already trust you.

327
00:22:06,960 --> 00:22:10,800
Your next step is to prove it
to your parents that you can do it.

328
00:22:14,360 --> 00:22:17,360
I know how painful it is
when your parents look down on you

329
00:22:17,920 --> 00:22:20,000
and don't believe in you.

330
00:22:29,120 --> 00:22:30,880
Let's fight together.

331
00:22:37,800 --> 00:22:39,320
Stop crying.

332
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:40,760
-I'm not a crybaby.
-Stop crying.

333
00:22:40,840 --> 00:22:42,000
I'm not crying.

334
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:07,920
Dad!

335
00:23:11,680 --> 00:23:13,280
Your hand is numb again?

336
00:23:13,360 --> 00:23:14,920
Yeah, it's numb again.

337
00:23:16,280 --> 00:23:18,760
Probably that tendon issue
the doctor mentioned.

338
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:20,760
You should go for surgery.

339
00:23:20,840 --> 00:23:22,240
Surgery?

340
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:26,600
Our schedule is packed.
There's money coming in.

341
00:23:26,680 --> 00:23:27,960
I'll just endure it for now.

342
00:23:32,680 --> 00:23:33,520
Dad.

343
00:23:35,120 --> 00:23:36,320
If I become rich

344
00:23:37,080 --> 00:23:38,560
and can take care of you,

345
00:23:39,320 --> 00:23:40,600
can you stop working?

346
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:45,400
Yuan.

347
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:48,080
Don't worry about me.

348
00:23:49,880 --> 00:23:52,040
I can work until I die
at the sewing machine.

349
00:23:54,360 --> 00:23:56,000
You just take care of yourself.

350
00:24:29,120 --> 00:24:32,080
<i>You want to start a clothing brand.</i>
<i>Do you understand design?</i>

351
00:24:32,160 --> 00:24:34,960
<i>Tailoring, pattern-making, sewing,</i>
<i>production capacity?</i>

352
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:37,880
<i>In the end, ask yourself this.</i>
<i>Do you want to be a clothing seller</i>

353
00:24:37,960 --> 00:24:40,320
<i>or a designer? They are not the same.</i>

354
00:24:55,480 --> 00:24:58,200
ONLINE FASHION DESIGN COURSE

355
00:25:26,160 --> 00:25:29,560
DAILY WAGE WORKERS

356
00:25:29,640 --> 00:25:31,720
SEARCH RESULTS

357
00:26:08,880 --> 00:26:11,280
I sent you the photos. Take a look.

358
00:26:11,960 --> 00:26:14,440
Congrats. You're so famous now.

359
00:26:14,520 --> 00:26:16,960
<i>Thanks, bestie.</i>

360
00:26:18,720 --> 00:26:22,640
<i>Hey, you're still working</i>
<i>with that Cent guy?</i>

361
00:26:24,240 --> 00:26:27,720
After what he did to us yesterday,
you're still okay with it?

362
00:26:28,720 --> 00:26:31,600
Not really.

363
00:26:31,680 --> 00:26:34,920
But he has his reasons.
I kind of understand him.

364
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:38,760
But I don't get it.
Why does he have to be that harsh?

365
00:26:38,840 --> 00:26:41,120
<i>He's so rude.</i>

366
00:26:41,200 --> 00:26:44,040
<i>We don't have to put up</i>
<i>with a boss like that, you know.</i>

367
00:26:44,560 --> 00:26:47,440
<i>You're talented. You have options.</i>

368
00:26:48,360 --> 00:26:52,200
The work you're helping him with
isn't even what you want to do, right?

369
00:26:53,800 --> 00:26:56,240
So, have you even started doing
your own work yet?

370
00:26:56,320 --> 00:26:57,320
Not yet.

371
00:26:57,400 --> 00:27:01,680
See? In the end,
you're just giving up your dream

372
00:27:02,720 --> 00:27:06,440
and sticking with a rude boss like that.
Why are you even putting up with it?

373
00:27:07,200 --> 00:27:09,400
No, it's not really putting up with it.

374
00:27:09,480 --> 00:27:12,920
He hasn't said anything so harsh
that I can't handle it.

375
00:27:14,960 --> 00:27:15,960
Well,

376
00:27:16,960 --> 00:27:18,480
if he does,

377
00:27:19,080 --> 00:27:20,560
<i>would you still put up with it?</i>

378
00:27:31,760 --> 00:27:33,160
Is that all you can do?

379
00:27:35,600 --> 00:27:37,240
"Is that all"?

380
00:27:39,280 --> 00:27:42,400
But it's almost 500 pages.

381
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:46,080
I searched every website
and printed everything out.

382
00:27:46,160 --> 00:27:49,800
If you just Google and print everything,
I don't need to hire you.

383
00:27:50,440 --> 00:27:51,560
I could do it myself.

384
00:27:53,080 --> 00:27:56,440
But you said you wanted information. So,

385
00:27:56,960 --> 00:27:58,320
I brought information.

386
00:27:58,400 --> 00:28:00,160
You don't understand the task I gave you.

387
00:28:00,240 --> 00:28:01,880
If you're going to do it this way,

388
00:28:01,960 --> 00:28:04,200
you should at least organize it,

389
00:28:04,280 --> 00:28:06,880
separate it into lifestyle, areas,

390
00:28:06,960 --> 00:28:09,480
occupations, and income levels. And this…

391
00:28:11,240 --> 00:28:13,560
Why are you including data from 2017?

392
00:28:16,920 --> 00:28:19,960
Then why didn't you just say this
from the start?

393
00:28:24,240 --> 00:28:27,880
I thought you could figure it out.
Turns out you can't.

394
00:28:32,680 --> 00:28:36,240
I've never done this before.
How was I supposed to know what to do?

395
00:28:36,320 --> 00:28:39,600
You've never done it, so you can't do it?
Then I'll just hire someone else.

396
00:28:41,160 --> 00:28:44,400
I told you from the beginning.
This is urgent and very important.

397
00:28:44,480 --> 00:28:46,640
I don't have time to train beginners.

398
00:28:46,720 --> 00:28:50,160
If you're not ready,
you shouldn't have taken the job.

399
00:28:50,240 --> 00:28:54,120
And if this is all you could do,
you should rethink what you're doing.

400
00:29:09,480 --> 00:29:11,120
I did my best…

401
00:29:13,120 --> 00:29:16,880
with the task you gave me.
This is really all I could do.

402
00:29:19,200 --> 00:29:21,480
So I'd like to step back and resign.

403
00:30:24,120 --> 00:30:24,960
Fired?

404
00:30:25,040 --> 00:30:27,280
I didn't fire her.
She resigned on her own.

405
00:30:27,360 --> 00:30:30,200
What did you say to her
for her to quit like that?

406
00:30:32,960 --> 00:30:34,400
I just said…

407
00:30:38,480 --> 00:30:40,080
"Is that all you can do?

408
00:30:40,640 --> 00:30:42,640
If it's just Googling,
I could do it myself."

409
00:30:48,360 --> 00:30:51,000
She said I didn't explain.

410
00:30:51,600 --> 00:30:53,760
So I asked her why
she couldn't figure it out.

411
00:30:54,880 --> 00:30:57,360
I already told her
this was urgent and very important.

412
00:30:57,440 --> 00:30:59,600
If she can't do it,
I'll just find someone else.

413
00:31:00,200 --> 00:31:01,000
-That's it.
-Geez.

414
00:31:01,080 --> 00:31:04,920
If someone talked to me like that,
I'd resign too.

415
00:31:05,680 --> 00:31:07,960
I was just stating facts.
I didn't insult her at all.

416
00:31:09,120 --> 00:31:13,560
The speaker says it's not an insult,
but the listener feels so attacked.

417
00:31:13,640 --> 00:31:14,480
Yes.

418
00:31:14,560 --> 00:31:16,920
-That bad?
-Yes.

419
00:31:18,560 --> 00:31:20,520
-Is it really that harsh?
-Very harsh!

420
00:31:36,480 --> 00:31:39,640
<i>I told you from the beginning.</i>
<i>This is urgent and very important.</i>

421
00:31:39,720 --> 00:31:42,160
<i>I don't have time to train beginners.</i>

422
00:31:42,240 --> 00:31:45,360
<i>If you're not ready,</i>
<i>you shouldn't have taken the job.</i>

423
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:49,480
<i>And if this is all you could do,</i>
<i>you should rethink what you're doing.</i>

424
00:32:09,760 --> 00:32:11,160
It's because you're like this

425
00:32:12,080 --> 00:32:15,040
that your partner says
you can't manage your team.

426
00:32:23,160 --> 00:32:24,440
Then what am I supposed to do?

427
00:32:25,040 --> 00:32:28,120
You want me to be all nice and sweet,
praise bad work,

428
00:32:28,200 --> 00:32:30,920
then secretly fix everything myself?

429
00:32:31,440 --> 00:32:33,320
How are they supposed
to grow or learn from that?

430
00:32:34,560 --> 00:32:37,320
And what have they actually learned
from the way you do it?

431
00:32:39,520 --> 00:32:40,960
You don't have to be overly sweet.

432
00:32:41,800 --> 00:32:43,800
But before you say anything,

433
00:32:43,880 --> 00:32:45,960
try to think
about how the other person will feel.

434
00:32:47,080 --> 00:32:48,520
Yes.

435
00:32:48,600 --> 00:32:51,960
Your mom is very direct,
even harsh sometimes.

436
00:32:52,040 --> 00:32:54,160
But I've never felt hurt by her.

437
00:32:54,240 --> 00:32:57,080
Because I know
she criticizes me out of care

438
00:32:57,160 --> 00:33:00,840
and teaches me with good intentions.
I've never been angry at her.

439
00:33:01,880 --> 00:33:04,240
You hired Fuang

440
00:33:04,320 --> 00:33:06,240
because you believed she could do the job.

441
00:33:08,040 --> 00:33:09,840
But you made it sound
like it was my decision,

442
00:33:09,920 --> 00:33:12,600
like I forced you into it.

443
00:33:15,920 --> 00:33:17,000
Honestly,

444
00:33:17,600 --> 00:33:21,800
if you didn't believe in her,
if you didn't see her potential,

445
00:33:21,880 --> 00:33:25,040
someone like you would never have agreed.

446
00:33:31,240 --> 00:33:32,720
How are you feeling right now?

447
00:33:47,560 --> 00:33:48,840
I feel…

448
00:33:50,120 --> 00:33:51,920
I feel sad, Dad.

449
00:33:52,000 --> 00:33:53,520
Because of what?

450
00:33:56,040 --> 00:33:58,440
It feels like I didn't do a good job.

451
00:33:59,280 --> 00:34:02,760
Like I'm not capable of anything.

452
00:34:02,840 --> 00:34:04,240
It hurts my confidence, Dad.

453
00:34:04,880 --> 00:34:06,880
And did you really do a bad job?

454
00:34:07,600 --> 00:34:11,600
I think it was good, Dad.
I worked really hard.

455
00:34:12,400 --> 00:34:14,239
It was a stack of information.
You saw it too.

456
00:34:14,320 --> 00:34:15,840
Did you read it all?

457
00:34:24,920 --> 00:34:26,679
I did read it.

458
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:30,480
But just quickly.

459
00:34:30,560 --> 00:34:32,920
Reading it quickly
means it's not thorough.

460
00:34:33,960 --> 00:34:36,440
A lot of information
doesn't mean good information.

461
00:34:38,360 --> 00:34:40,360
But he only gave me one day.

462
00:34:42,880 --> 00:34:43,880
Because of the limited time?

463
00:34:44,719 --> 00:34:47,480
That's why, if your boss
criticizes your work,

464
00:34:48,920 --> 00:34:50,600
you have to accept that first.

465
00:34:54,679 --> 00:34:58,240
I used to work in editing.
I've been through this a lot.

466
00:34:58,840 --> 00:35:01,760
Especially as a freelancer,
we have to adapt.

467
00:35:02,320 --> 00:35:04,680
Every time someone comments on our work,

468
00:35:04,760 --> 00:35:06,640
we should first ask ourselves,

469
00:35:07,800 --> 00:35:09,320
did we do our best?

470
00:35:14,840 --> 00:35:17,120
But what if we already did our best

471
00:35:17,200 --> 00:35:19,160
and it still isn't good enough?

472
00:35:23,120 --> 00:35:26,840
Then you have to be sure
you truly did your best.

473
00:35:27,520 --> 00:35:30,560
If it really is your full effort
and it still isn't okay,

474
00:35:31,720 --> 00:35:33,040
maybe you have to step back.

475
00:35:35,400 --> 00:35:36,800
If it's not your full effort yet,

476
00:35:38,240 --> 00:35:39,880
then you need to think again,

477
00:35:40,640 --> 00:35:43,760
whether to give up or start over.

478
00:35:44,360 --> 00:35:47,160
That's something
you have to decide for yourself.

479
00:36:08,640 --> 00:36:09,840
Cent?

480
00:36:12,440 --> 00:36:13,280
Where are you going?

481
00:36:15,720 --> 00:36:16,840
I'm…

482
00:36:18,960 --> 00:36:20,240
But what are you doing here?

483
00:36:23,560 --> 00:36:25,520
You answer first. Where are you going?

484
00:36:26,720 --> 00:36:27,840
Well…

485
00:36:30,800 --> 00:36:33,000
I was going to see you.

486
00:36:35,040 --> 00:36:35,880
Why?

487
00:36:36,600 --> 00:36:39,960
Hey, no cheating.
You still haven't told me why you're here.

488
00:36:53,960 --> 00:36:55,680
Okay! I'll apologize first.

489
00:36:56,920 --> 00:36:59,360
I'm sorry that I didn't
do my job well enough.

490
00:36:59,440 --> 00:37:01,080
Sorry for being too impulsive back then.

491
00:37:01,160 --> 00:37:02,560
-And I'm sorry that--
-Enough, Fuang.

492
00:37:02,640 --> 00:37:04,160
You don't need to apologize anymore.

493
00:37:07,200 --> 00:37:09,560
It's my fault. I was too harsh.

494
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:14,680
Anyway, I'm sorry too.

495
00:37:18,320 --> 00:37:19,480
What's with that face?

496
00:37:26,160 --> 00:37:27,320
I'm happy.

497
00:37:28,080 --> 00:37:30,000
I'm happy that you're not mad.

498
00:37:35,360 --> 00:37:36,240
Cent.

499
00:37:36,840 --> 00:37:40,920
Can I have another chance to fix it?
Can I do the work again?

500
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:42,920
I'll do it better than before.

501
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:45,880
Now I know where I went wrong
and what I need to fix.

502
00:37:47,560 --> 00:37:49,480
Can I have another chance?

503
00:37:51,240 --> 00:37:52,360
Okay.

504
00:37:55,200 --> 00:37:57,920
Okay, just like that?

505
00:38:00,560 --> 00:38:01,960
Honestly,

506
00:38:03,440 --> 00:38:04,840
even if you hadn't asked,

507
00:38:06,000 --> 00:38:07,880
I was going to ask you to return anyway.

508
00:38:13,600 --> 00:38:16,160
Don't look at me like that. I mean it.

509
00:38:21,240 --> 00:38:22,680
Did Aunt Eiang force you to come?

510
00:38:26,200 --> 00:38:27,200
No.

511
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:28,880
I decided on my own.

512
00:38:32,640 --> 00:38:34,920
I believe you can do better than this.

513
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:39,800
Even if you didn't ask
for a second chance,

514
00:38:42,760 --> 00:38:44,320
I would've given it to you anyway.

515
00:38:47,800 --> 00:38:49,120
Give it another try.

516
00:38:57,200 --> 00:39:01,040
Thank you. Thank you so much.

517
00:39:09,160 --> 00:39:10,880
Thank you so much.

518
00:39:17,560 --> 00:39:20,320
Thank you for believing in me, Cent.

519
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:30,320
I'll go tell my parents first.

520
00:39:31,600 --> 00:39:32,480
Thank you again.

521
00:39:45,400 --> 00:39:49,000
Okay, that's good.
Tell Fuang I'm rooting for her too.

522
00:39:49,080 --> 00:39:53,080
If there are any problems,
just let me know.

523
00:39:55,720 --> 00:39:58,080
I've finished packing everything.

524
00:39:58,160 --> 00:39:59,320
Yeah.

525
00:39:59,840 --> 00:40:03,800
Fuang's your friend's daughter.
Why are you so interested in her work?

526
00:40:05,480 --> 00:40:06,680
Are you trying to set them up?

527
00:40:06,760 --> 00:40:08,480
-Huh?
-Yeah?

528
00:40:09,760 --> 00:40:12,400
I'm not thinking that far, Pong.

529
00:40:13,440 --> 00:40:16,640
Love can't be forced.

530
00:40:18,320 --> 00:40:20,480
I just want Cent to have a social life

531
00:40:20,560 --> 00:40:22,800
and learn to interact with others.

532
00:40:23,400 --> 00:40:25,440
Hey, and Fuang

533
00:40:25,520 --> 00:40:28,560
is a nice, kind girl.

534
00:40:28,640 --> 00:40:30,760
If she can just get him out there
to see the world

535
00:40:30,840 --> 00:40:33,040
and meet people, that's enough for me.

536
00:40:34,600 --> 00:40:37,520
Now I want to see Fuang's face.
Is she cute?

537
00:40:40,800 --> 00:40:42,120
As cute as me?

538
00:40:43,680 --> 00:40:44,720
What?

539
00:40:53,440 --> 00:40:54,320
Hey.

540
00:40:54,400 --> 00:40:56,120
Pong!

541
00:41:00,480 --> 00:41:03,560
<i>If not online,</i>
<i>where else can we find information?</i>

542
00:41:03,640 --> 00:41:07,000
<i>The library. Or just do interviews.</i>

543
00:41:07,080 --> 00:41:11,520
<i>They say each country has an agency</i>
<i>that calculates the poverty line.</i>

544
00:41:11,600 --> 00:41:13,960
<i>Any country whose monthly income</i>
<i>falls below that line</i>

545
00:41:14,040 --> 00:41:15,760
<i>is considered poor.</i>

546
00:41:15,840 --> 00:41:19,200
<i>Whoa. Then our family</i>
<i>is definitely below that line.</i>

547
00:41:20,960 --> 00:41:22,560
<i>Who calculates it, Mom?</i>

548
00:41:22,640 --> 00:41:26,840
<i>The Office of the National Economic</i>
<i>and Social Development Council.</i>

549
00:41:26,920 --> 00:41:30,280
Excuse me. Where can I find
information about the economy?

550
00:41:30,360 --> 00:41:32,800
<i>Besides the poverty line,</i>

551
00:41:32,880 --> 00:41:36,200
<i>they also calculate income in detail.</i>

552
00:41:36,280 --> 00:41:39,800
It's divided into five groups.
The poorest,

553
00:41:39,880 --> 00:41:40,760
the less poor…

554
00:41:40,840 --> 00:41:41,680
POOREST, LESS POOR, MIDDLE CLASS

555
00:41:41,760 --> 00:41:44,880
…the middle class, the upper class,
and the highest-income group.

556
00:41:45,480 --> 00:41:50,240
Someday, we're going to move up
from where we are.

557
00:41:50,320 --> 00:41:52,320
To the highest-income group?

558
00:41:52,400 --> 00:41:54,840
We'll move up from the poorest

559
00:41:54,920 --> 00:41:56,200
to the less poor first.

560
00:41:58,320 --> 00:41:59,560
-Whoa!
-Dad!

561
00:41:59,640 --> 00:42:02,000
Here, take this.

562
00:42:02,600 --> 00:42:04,200
What was it again?

563
00:42:04,280 --> 00:42:05,840
The less poor.

564
00:42:11,400 --> 00:42:13,640
This book isn't very relevant.

565
00:42:27,760 --> 00:42:29,040
Pound.

566
00:42:30,800 --> 00:42:31,680
Pound!

567
00:42:35,120 --> 00:42:36,160
Hey, Pound!

568
00:42:37,640 --> 00:42:38,800
Coming, Dad!

569
00:42:44,080 --> 00:42:45,200
What's going on, Dad?

570
00:42:45,280 --> 00:42:46,360
Pack your things.

571
00:42:47,120 --> 00:42:48,200
We're moving out of here.

572
00:42:50,400 --> 00:42:51,640
Moving out?

573
00:42:53,120 --> 00:42:54,960
Why do we have to move?
Where are we going?

574
00:42:55,040 --> 00:42:56,760
Can you just stop asking?

575
00:42:56,840 --> 00:42:59,720
Just do what I say.
Go pack your things now.

576
00:43:04,360 --> 00:43:07,160
Dad! You have to tell me why we're moving.

577
00:43:07,760 --> 00:43:09,120
And where are we going?

578
00:43:09,200 --> 00:43:11,640
If you don't tell me,
I'm not going anywhere and--

579
00:43:35,160 --> 00:43:36,320
What is this, Mom?

580
00:43:40,560 --> 00:43:42,040
Why are we moving?

581
00:43:45,080 --> 00:43:46,080
Dad.

582
00:43:48,800 --> 00:43:51,480
I don't want
just your orders anymore, Dad.

583
00:43:52,080 --> 00:43:54,760
I need to know exactly what's going on.

584
00:44:01,160 --> 00:44:02,640
If you have something to say, say it!

585
00:44:03,240 --> 00:44:05,440
Don't be a coward, Dad. Just tell me

586
00:44:05,960 --> 00:44:08,560
why we have to move. I can take it.

587
00:44:09,280 --> 00:44:10,880
What's going on?

588
00:44:12,400 --> 00:44:13,760
We're bankrupt.

589
00:44:16,640 --> 00:44:20,160
I've sold everything,
the factory, all the houses.

590
00:44:21,440 --> 00:44:23,640
It still wasn't enough
to pay the bank debt.

591
00:44:23,720 --> 00:44:25,520
We have nothing left.

592
00:44:26,920 --> 00:44:29,640
We need to pack and leave this place now.

593
00:44:38,520 --> 00:44:39,520
That's not true.

594
00:44:41,200 --> 00:44:42,080
It's true.

595
00:44:43,000 --> 00:44:45,000
You wanted to know the truth, right?

596
00:44:46,320 --> 00:44:47,760
Then face it.

597
00:44:48,640 --> 00:44:49,840
Go pack your things now.

598
00:44:58,920 --> 00:44:59,920
No.

599
00:45:08,280 --> 00:45:10,080
You don't get to order me around.

600
00:45:11,800 --> 00:45:13,600
I told you

601
00:45:14,400 --> 00:45:16,480
I was going to help at the factory.

602
00:45:17,480 --> 00:45:19,760
I could've saved it,

603
00:45:19,840 --> 00:45:22,200
but you ruined it, Dad.

604
00:45:23,600 --> 00:45:24,880
It failed because you're stubborn,

605
00:45:24,960 --> 00:45:27,320
old-fashioned, and you refuse to adapt.

606
00:45:27,400 --> 00:45:29,520
You refuse to accept you're out of touch.

607
00:45:30,120 --> 00:45:32,000
This is a new generation's world now.

608
00:45:32,080 --> 00:45:33,800
It's not yours anymore!

609
00:45:33,880 --> 00:45:35,400
-Pound!
-Pound!

610
00:45:35,480 --> 00:45:36,800
-Pound, dear!
-Pound!

611
00:45:36,880 --> 00:45:37,840
You think you're so good?

612
00:45:39,280 --> 00:45:42,080
So impressive? Want another one?

613
00:45:42,160 --> 00:45:43,680
-Dad, please stop.
-Don't!

614
00:45:44,480 --> 00:45:46,640
That's enough. I'm begging you.

615
00:45:47,520 --> 00:45:48,720
And remember this.

616
00:45:49,880 --> 00:45:53,440
The house you lived in comfortably,
the expensive car,

617
00:45:53,520 --> 00:45:55,880
the money you've spent so freely
since you were a kid…

618
00:45:55,960 --> 00:45:57,720
They all came from this old-fashioned man.

619
00:45:57,800 --> 00:45:59,920
If you say this world

620
00:46:00,920 --> 00:46:03,800
belongs to your generation,

621
00:46:03,880 --> 00:46:05,640
then go make your own money.

622
00:46:05,720 --> 00:46:09,520
Don't take a single cent
from this old man again.

623
00:46:10,120 --> 00:46:12,280
And don't you ever think

624
00:46:12,800 --> 00:46:14,560
you're the only one

625
00:46:15,800 --> 00:46:17,800
who's suffering because you're my son.

626
00:46:19,960 --> 00:46:21,400
As your father,

627
00:46:23,160 --> 00:46:25,920
having a son like you
stand there and yell at me,

628
00:46:26,680 --> 00:46:28,480
it hurts me too.

629
00:46:44,120 --> 00:46:45,440
Pound.

630
00:46:46,240 --> 00:46:48,840
Please do as your dad says.

631
00:46:49,600 --> 00:46:52,160
Pack up and move out for now, okay?

632
00:46:55,120 --> 00:46:57,560
Where are we going to live, Mom?

633
00:47:00,560 --> 00:47:02,400
I've already found a rental place.

634
00:47:02,920 --> 00:47:05,400
We'll stay there temporarily.

635
00:47:06,040 --> 00:47:08,400
Then we'll figure out what to do next.

636
00:47:11,000 --> 00:47:12,240
Dear. Pung.

637
00:47:13,640 --> 00:47:14,960
Come help me with this.

638
00:47:15,920 --> 00:47:17,200
Yes.

639
00:48:07,480 --> 00:48:09,240
DAY MARKETS, NIGHT MARKETS

640
00:48:46,120 --> 00:48:47,240
Fuang!

641
00:48:55,680 --> 00:49:00,080
The work you assigned
is already on the visual board.

642
00:49:00,160 --> 00:49:02,760
Yeah, I see it.

643
00:49:05,440 --> 00:49:09,160
What are you going to assign me today?
Just tell me.

644
00:49:10,000 --> 00:49:12,320
Nothing. You can go home.

645
00:49:14,800 --> 00:49:17,560
Are you sending me home or firing me?

646
00:49:19,840 --> 00:49:21,200
I'm sending you home.

647
00:49:26,040 --> 00:49:29,000
You worked all night, didn't you?

648
00:49:31,680 --> 00:49:32,880
Yes.

649
00:49:33,560 --> 00:49:34,920
Then go home and rest.

650
00:49:37,760 --> 00:49:39,080
Thank you.

651
00:49:39,680 --> 00:49:43,000
I'll head home now, then.

652
00:49:44,640 --> 00:49:45,720
Okay.

653
00:50:54,920 --> 00:50:58,640
So after tasting everything,
which ones did you like?

654
00:50:59,240 --> 00:51:01,040
I think I like these two the most.

655
00:51:01,120 --> 00:51:02,040
Okay.

656
00:51:02,120 --> 00:51:03,160
This one is too sweet.

657
00:51:03,240 --> 00:51:04,200
Like, very sweet?

658
00:51:04,280 --> 00:51:07,360
A bit too sweet.
I can't really explain it.

659
00:51:07,440 --> 00:51:10,560
This one is slightly too sour.
Maybe because of the orange, I'm not sure.

660
00:51:10,640 --> 00:51:11,880
It's an orange cake, though.

661
00:51:11,960 --> 00:51:13,040
-Yeah.
-Right.

662
00:51:13,120 --> 00:51:17,000
And this one,
I think the texture feels a bit rough.

663
00:51:17,600 --> 00:51:18,480
What about you, Fuang?

664
00:51:18,560 --> 00:51:22,080
For me, this one isn't too sweet at all.
It's just right.

665
00:51:22,160 --> 00:51:23,480
You think it's okay already?

666
00:51:23,560 --> 00:51:27,000
And the orange cake is a bit sour,
even though it's orange.

667
00:51:27,080 --> 00:51:28,120
-Really?
-Right?

668
00:51:28,200 --> 00:51:29,320
Yeah. Just a little, though.

669
00:51:29,400 --> 00:51:31,200
-Just a little.
-Just a little.

670
00:51:31,280 --> 00:51:33,720
-We actually like the other ones.
-Yeah.

671
00:51:35,200 --> 00:51:37,000
Thanks, guys.

672
00:51:37,080 --> 00:51:38,960
I'll try to adjust the recipe.

673
00:51:39,040 --> 00:51:41,080
And once it's better,

674
00:51:41,160 --> 00:51:42,680
help me taste it again, okay?

675
00:51:43,520 --> 00:51:45,000
-Sure.
-Hey, Yuan.

676
00:51:45,080 --> 00:51:47,360
-Huh?
-How's your online course going?

677
00:51:47,440 --> 00:51:50,560
Harder than I thought.
I'm starting from scratch with drawing.

678
00:51:51,120 --> 00:51:52,160
Still a long way to go.

679
00:51:52,240 --> 00:51:54,360
I think you don't need
to study it so much.

680
00:51:54,440 --> 00:51:55,760
If you want to do it, just do it.

681
00:51:56,480 --> 00:52:00,520
Look at me. If I had listened to Cent,

682
00:52:00,600 --> 00:52:02,840
I probably wouldn't have started
anything by now.

683
00:52:03,760 --> 00:52:06,800
Hey, I don't mean he's not good, okay?

684
00:52:06,880 --> 00:52:09,320
We just have different ways of thinking.

685
00:52:11,200 --> 00:52:13,960
I think you just have to try
and learn by doing.

686
00:52:14,040 --> 00:52:16,280
You've got Pound backing you financially.

687
00:52:16,360 --> 00:52:17,960
I don't have an investor.

688
00:52:18,040 --> 00:52:20,000
If I want to start, I can't just start.

689
00:52:20,600 --> 00:52:21,840
But me…

690
00:52:21,920 --> 00:52:24,000
I still haven't gotten anywhere.

691
00:52:26,360 --> 00:52:28,000
Once I finish Cent's work,
I have to start too.

692
00:52:39,080 --> 00:52:42,040
Is this a house or a storage room?
How can we live in a place this small?

693
00:52:42,120 --> 00:52:43,680
If you can't live here, then don't.

694
00:53:28,440 --> 00:53:29,800
Eat something simple first, okay?

695
00:53:30,680 --> 00:53:33,480
Tomorrow I'll go to the supermarket
and buy some groceries.

696
00:53:33,560 --> 00:53:34,880
No.

697
00:53:39,040 --> 00:53:41,560
I'm not really hungry.

698
00:53:45,720 --> 00:53:46,720
I can't eat.

699
00:53:53,360 --> 00:53:55,000
Just hang in there, okay?

700
00:54:14,080 --> 00:54:15,000
No.

701
00:54:19,840 --> 00:54:21,120
I won't just hang in there.

702
00:54:25,280 --> 00:54:28,160
I'll do whatever it takes
to make money, Mom.

703
00:54:30,960 --> 00:54:34,040
Our family is going to be rich again.

704
00:55:16,800 --> 00:55:17,680
How's it going?

705
00:55:17,760 --> 00:55:19,440
-Did you wait long?
-Hey, Suea.

706
00:55:19,520 --> 00:55:21,080
-Hello.
-Hi.

707
00:55:22,440 --> 00:55:23,760
Thank you so much for coming.

708
00:55:23,840 --> 00:55:25,920
It's okay. No need to worry.

709
00:55:26,000 --> 00:55:28,920
I told you already. If you want to invest,
I'll coach you myself.

710
00:55:29,520 --> 00:55:31,560
I want to go full-time trading.

711
00:55:31,640 --> 00:55:34,200
I want to be like you, a full-time trader.

712
00:55:34,280 --> 00:55:35,960
I want to get rich as fast as possible.

713
00:55:36,560 --> 00:55:38,640
How much is in your portfolio right now?

714
00:55:39,640 --> 00:55:41,240
Around 500,000 baht.

715
00:55:42,840 --> 00:55:46,680
What about your relatives, friends,
people around you? How much do they have?

716
00:55:48,320 --> 00:55:50,560
Actually, no one around me trades.

717
00:55:51,200 --> 00:55:54,240
But if I invite them,
I think they'd be interested.

718
00:55:54,920 --> 00:55:57,320
If you manage portfolios
for people you know,

719
00:55:57,960 --> 00:55:59,000
how much do you think you'll make?

720
00:56:03,480 --> 00:56:06,400
Wow. Quite a lot, actually.

721
00:56:06,480 --> 00:56:07,920
Probably in the millions, I think.

722
00:56:08,680 --> 00:56:10,240
Good. That's good.

723
00:56:11,440 --> 00:56:12,640
Thank you.

724
00:56:13,480 --> 00:56:14,680
Then I suggest

725
00:56:15,400 --> 00:56:17,720
you build your own capital up
to at least one million baht.

726
00:56:17,800 --> 00:56:19,800
But you'll need to get
your IC License first.

727
00:56:19,880 --> 00:56:22,560
Once you have it, I'll introduce you
to my friend's brokerage.

728
00:56:23,160 --> 00:56:24,800
That way, you can trade
for people close to you.

729
00:56:25,400 --> 00:56:27,480
With this kind of thing,
you can't get rich alone.

730
00:56:28,080 --> 00:56:29,080
-We'll get rich together!
-We'll get rich together!

731
00:56:32,800 --> 00:56:34,600
-Very good.
-Thank you.

732
00:56:35,200 --> 00:56:37,360
<i>I'm going out of town.</i>
<i>Not sure when I'll be back.</i>

733
00:56:37,440 --> 00:56:39,920
<i>Don't worry. Just spend</i>
<i>your time working for me.</i>

734
00:56:40,000 --> 00:56:42,560
<i>Go live your life.</i>
<i>When you finish the job,</i>

735
00:56:42,640 --> 00:56:44,440
<i>you'll get my shares for sure.</i>

736
00:56:44,520 --> 00:56:46,360
I've set the profit margin too low, Mom.

737
00:56:50,360 --> 00:56:51,760
I should make it 100%.

738
00:56:53,480 --> 00:56:54,440
Move your bag off the laptop.

739
00:56:55,440 --> 00:56:57,080
Can't you see something's there?

740
00:56:57,680 --> 00:56:59,760
It's just a light bag.
It's fine sitting there.

741
00:57:00,760 --> 00:57:01,760
What's the big deal?

742
00:57:02,360 --> 00:57:04,080
That's exactly why you're so shallow.

743
00:57:04,600 --> 00:57:08,040
You want to be an influencer,
but you don't know what an influencer is.

744
00:57:08,120 --> 00:57:10,880
We're not even close enough
for you to talk to me like that.

745
00:57:10,960 --> 00:57:11,960
Learn some manners.

746
00:57:12,040 --> 00:57:15,240
And the person who puts their bag
on someone else's laptop has manners?

747
00:57:58,800 --> 00:58:01,160
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
